2. Methodology and Research Framework

The ICSP employs a hybridized analytical model combining:

* Macroeconomic Dependency Inversion (MDI)
* Hostile Supply Loop Modeling (HSLM)
* Applied Irony Metrics (AIM v4.2)

Primary simulation environments were constructed using the Global Conflict Spreadsheet (GCS), wherein each nation’s wartime capability is calculated as:

Combat Readiness = Domestic Production ÷ Imported Necessity²

This formula collapses under all known Western conditions, producing either zero or negative readiness values, indicating pre-emptive logistical surrender.

A secondary framework, the Boomerang Armament Principle (BAP), posits that:

“All weapons systems, when sufficiently globalized, possess an inherent tendency to return to their point of manufacture, either physically or economically.”

Case modeling demonstrates that a British tank constructed using imported Chinese steel, powered by Russian fuel, and guided by Taiwanese semiconductors, constitutes a multilateral diplomatic incident prior to ignition.

